casebody.data:
The Wilber National Bank of Oneonta, New York, respondent, v. John F. Betz, Impleaded, &c., appellant. Decided February 4, 1884. Appeal by defendant from an order denying bis motion to set aside order for publication of summons. Samuel Untermyer, for appellant; Estes & Barnard, for respondent.

Before Sedgwick, Ch. J., Freedman and O’Gorman, JJ.

Per Curiam.

Order affirmed, with $10 costs and disbursements to be taxed.
